{
  "texts": [
    "The exclusive focus on the SpamAssassin public mail corpus may not fully capture the complexities of spam detection in diverse real-world scenarios.",
    "Additionally, the evaluation was conducted on unmodified versions of ChatGPT-4 and Google Gemini, which does not account for potential improvements through fine-tuning or adaptation to specific spam detection contexts.",
    "These limitations suggest that further research should consider a broader array of datasets and explore the impact of model customization on performance outcomes.",
    "E. Future Research DirectionsLooking ahead, future research should aim to address the identified limitations by incorporating a wider variety of spam datasets, including those from social media platforms, instant messaging services, and emerging communication technologies.",
    "Investigating the effects of fine-tuning the models on specific types of spam could unveil opportunities to enhance their accuracy and adaptability."
  ]
}